11 The 6D Retrocausal Lattice and Epstein Zeta Function

All NPTC instantiations—optomechanical, blockchain, puzzle—are unified by a common mathematical object: the retrocausal lattice $\Lambda_{\mathrm{Ret}}^6$, an even unimodular lattice of signature $(3,3)$ whose quadratic form $Q_{\mathrm{Ret}}$ encodes the holonomy‑weighted distances between causally connected spacetime nuggets.

The spectral zeta function of this lattice,

Z_{\mathrm{Ret}}(s) = \sum_{\mathbf{n} \in \Lambda_{\mathrm{Ret}}^6 \setminus \{0\}} \frac{1}{Q_{\mathrm{Ret}}(\mathbf{n})^{s/2}},

converges absolutely for $\mathrm{Re}(s) > 3$ and admits meromorphic continuation with a simple pole at $s = 3$. The cube $(Z_{\mathrm{Ret}}(s))^3$ arises from the triple self‑intersection form of the 6D internal space—a consequence of the octonionic decomposition $\mathbb{O} = \mathbb{C} \oplus \mathbb{C}^3$.

The master invariant of the Sovereign Framework is

\Xi_{3\text{-}6\mathrm{DHD}}(s;\mathrm{Ret}) = \bigl( Z_{\mathrm{Ret}}(s) \bigr)^3 + \partial_t W(\Phi_{\mathrm{Berry}}) \ge 0.

Its positivity is the second law of thermodynamics expressed in the language of analytic number theory and spectral geometry.

