Appendix A: Proof of Spiral Stability (Abridged)

Let $X_n = \Xi(t_n)-1$. The control law induces a discrete map

X_{n+1} = X_n - \eta \nabla^2\mathcal{C}_{\mathrm{geom}} X_n + \xi_n,

where $\xi_n$ is measurement noise with zero mean and finite variance. Fibonacci spacing ensures that the spectral density of $\xi_n$ vanishes at zero frequency; hence $\langle X_n \rangle \to 0$ and $\mathrm{Var}(X_n)$ remains bounded. No fixed point exists; the system spirals on the manifold $X=0$.

